        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 24 at 8:17PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 817 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Happy, or 9 miles southeast of Canyon, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wayside and Palo Duro Canyon.

This includes Interstate 27 between mile markers 91 and 101.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
